verses.text:
And the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* spake unto Moses , Go unto Pharaoh , and say unto him, Thus saith the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, Let my people go , that they may serve me.
And if thou refuse to let \add them\add* go , behold, I will smite all thy borders with frogs :

And the river shall bring forth frogs abundantly , which shall go up and come into thine house , and into thy bedchamber , and upon thy bed , and into the house of thy servants , and upon thy people , and into thine ovens , and into thy kneadingtroughs :\f + \fr 8.3 \ft kneadingtroughs: or, dough\f*
And the frogs shall come up both on thee, and upon thy people , and upon all thy servants. \p

¶ And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* spake unto Moses , Say unto Aaron , Stretch forth thine hand with thy rod over the streams , over the rivers , and over the ponds , and cause frogs to come up upon the land of Egypt.
And Aaron stretched out his hand over the waters of Egypt ; and the frogs came up , and covered the land of Egypt.
And the magicians did so with their enchantments , and brought up frogs upon the land of Egypt. \p

¶ Then Pharaoh called for Moses and Aaron , and said , Intreat the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, that he may take away the frogs from me, and from my people ; and I will let the people go , that they may do sacrifice unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*.

And Moses said unto Pharaoh , Glory over me: when shall I intreat for thee, and for thy servants , and for thy people , to destroy the frogs from thee and thy houses , \add that\add* they may remain in the river only?\f + \fr 8.9 \ft Glory…: or, Have this honour over me, etc\f*\f + \fr 8.9 \ft when: or, against when\f*\f + \fr 8.9 \ft to destroy: Heb. to cut off\f*

And he said , To morrow. And he said , \add Be it\add* according to thy word : that thou mayest know that \add there is\add* none like unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* our God.\f + \fr 8.10 \ft To morrow: or, Against to morrow\f*
And the frogs shall depart from thee, and from thy houses , and from thy servants , and from thy people ; they shall remain in the river only.
And Moses and Aaron went out from Pharaoh : and Moses cried unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* because of the frogs which he had brought against Pharaoh.
And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* did according to the word of Moses ; and the frogs died out of the houses , out of the villages , and out of the fields.
And they gathered them together upon heaps : and the land stank.
But when Pharaoh saw that there was respite , he hardened his heart , and hearkened not unto them; as the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* had said. \p
¶ And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* said unto Moses , Say unto Aaron , Stretch out thy rod , and smite the dust of the land , that it may become lice throughout all the land of Egypt.

And they did so; for Aaron stretched out his hand with his rod , and smote the dust of the earth , and it became lice in man , and in beast ; all the dust of the land became lice throughout all the land of Egypt.
And the magicians did so with their enchantments to bring forth lice , but they could not: so there were lice upon man , and upon beast.
Then the magicians said unto Pharaoh , This \add is\add* the finger of God : and Pharaoh’s heart was hardened , and he hearkened not unto them; as the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* had said. \p

¶ And the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* said unto Moses , Rise up early in the morning , and stand before Pharaoh ; lo, he cometh forth to the water ; and say unto him, Thus saith the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, Let my people go , that they may serve me.

Else, if thou wilt not let my people go , behold, I will send swarms \add of flies\add* upon thee, and upon thy servants , and upon thy people , and into thy houses : and the houses of the Egyptians shall be full of swarms \add of flies\add*, and also the ground whereon they \add are\add*.\f + \fr 8.21 \ft swarms…: or, a mixture of noisome beasts, etc\f*

And I will sever in that day the land of Goshen , in which my people dwell , that no swarms \add of flies\add* shall be there; to the end thou mayest know that I \add am\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* in the midst of the earth.
And I will put a division between my people and thy people : to morrow shall this sign be.\f + \fr 8.23 \ft a division: Heb. a redemption\f*\f + \fr 8.23 \ft to morrow: or, by to morrow\f*

And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* did so; and there came a grievous swarm \add of flies\add* into the house of Pharaoh , and \add into\add* his servants’ houses , and into all the land of Egypt : the land was corrupted by reason of the swarm \add of flies\add*.\f + \fr 8.24 \ft corrupted: or, destroyed\f* \p
¶ And Pharaoh called for Moses and for Aaron , and said , Go ye, sacrifice to your God in the land.

And Moses said , It is not meet so to do ; for we shall sacrifice the abomination of the Egyptians to the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* our God : lo, shall we sacrifice the abomination of the Egyptians before their eyes , and will they not stone us?
We will go three days’ journey into the wilderness , and sacrifice to the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* our God , as he shall command us.
And Pharaoh said , I will let you go , that ye may sacrifice to the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* your God in the wilderness ; only ye shall not go very far away : intreat for me.

And Moses said , Behold, I go out from thee, and I will intreat the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* that the swarms \add of flies\add* may depart from Pharaoh , from his servants , and from his people , to morrow : but let not Pharaoh deal deceitfully any more in not letting the people go to sacrifice to the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*.
And Moses went out from Pharaoh , and intreated the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.

And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* did according to the word of Moses ; and he removed the swarms \add of flies\add* from Pharaoh , from his servants , and from his people ; there remained not one.
And Pharaoh hardened his heart at this time also, neither would he let the people go.
